The article is a speech by OMB Director Peter Orszag addressing the Council on Foreign Relations. He discusses the economic stabilization and recovery efforts of the Obama administration, as well as the importance of health care reform in ensuring the nation's fiscal future. Orszag explains the severity of the economic crisis that the administration inherited and the measures taken to rescue the economy. He emphasizes the need to restore confidence and lays out the administration's strategy for sustained economic growth. Orszag also discusses the implementation and impact of the Recovery Act, addressing criticisms and highlighting the progress made. He acknowledges the challenges in reducing unemployment and the importance of transforming the healthcare system to one that delivers better care at lower costs. Orszag concludes by emphasizing the long road ahead in rebuilding the economy and the need for continued cooperation and hard work.